the old gentleman had expre&s;&s;ed his concern
about that affair; and, among other ob&s;erva|tions,
&s;aid, he &s;uppo&s;ed the object of his love was
&s;ome paultry hu&s;&s;y, whom he had picked up
when he was a boy at &s;chool. Upon which,
Mr. Hatchway a&s;&s;ured him, that &s;he was a young
