throughout the whole kingdom of Eng|land,
allowing the&s;e mini&s;ters a certain propor|tion
of the profits accruing from their indu&s;try
and &s;kill, and re&s;erving the greate&s;t &s;hare for the
benefit of the common &s;tock, which was charge|able
with the expence of fitting out individuals
in their various pur&s;uits, as well as with the lo&s;s
&s;u&s;tained in the cour&s;e of their adventures. Some,
who&s;e per&s;ons and qualifications are by the com|pany
